pageTitle: Chalk one up for Sharks | CedarKeyBeacon.com
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {34685=After an 0-9 start and a winless 2009-10 campaign, the young Sharks could have easily swam far away from the shores of Cedar Key, and into the secluded deep of the Gulf. But thanks to a loyal fanbase and the never-give-up hustle of its players, 1A Cedar Key was able to give the 2A Indians more than it bargained before while achieving a team goal in the process., 43961=Copyright © 2015, 36081=Sills' deep three-pointer from the right wing cut Chiefland's lead to 38-30 with 3:34 remaining in the third quarter. That was as close as the Sharks would get until a bucket by Sills at the 3:13 mark of the fourth quarter made it 55-46. However, the Indians would use offensive rebounds and turnovers to score the final 10 points of the game, including six by Bo Beauchamp, to put the game away.}
